^B@2^*BLarry Cohen: ^*N|cp||at|What should your partner do after your preempt? |
PG| ***** 15 ***** |


AT|This is easy. Follow the LAW! Raise to the proper LAW level |CP|1|AT|^*Hwww.larryco.com/bridge-learning-center/detail/129^*N|CP||AT|--just as he would over your opening preempt. |
PG| ***** 16 ***** |


AT|

If you want more science, you can play that 2NT after partner's jump overcall is artificial. You can use it for Feature ("Front of Card"), or you can use it to ask for shortness.  I find that this never comes up--not worth the memory strain.|
PG| ***** 17 ***** |


AT|

Whatever you do, stay in character. if you are a sound preemptor, don't change your style for jump overcalls. If partner expects you to have a good suit and a decent hand, don't start zigging and zagging. |
PG| ***** 18 ***** |


